Irons devotes pages to caricaturing the backgrounds, beliefs, and political affiliations of ID proponents, rather obviously trying to present ID as part of a nefarious conspiracy of the ÒReligious Right.Ó This is an example of what historian Richard Hofstadter called ÒThe Paranoid Style in American Politics.Ó7 Irons tries to avoid debating the real issues by poisoning the well.
